    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nails used for the wooden decks of ships or decks attached to buildings, usually having a neat square or round, flat head that beds in flush with the surface of the plank of wood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
